<br>
<br>
Its been hinted at here and there ... But the Rules that the RTA is currently working on for the most part ... are now Obsolete .... And gues what its finally starting to show on all levels ... Plus several Comments have been made by a few People , and I don't even know if they realize exactly what they have said ... <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Respect the no teaming recommendation by the rathe community, and wait a year or so to see the higher content. All that time losing members of your guild to the higher end guilds who have surpassed that content, and are the ones enforcing the &quot;no teaming&quot; ideal.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Gues what... This statement right here , doesn't just apply to Teaming on PoP mobs ... This statement applies to Everything that the RTA stands for ... Being Fair , and giving everyone equal Opportunity , and is reflected in Rotations , and the Current Rules for being a Posting Entity ... and if You try to counter it , with a no this doesn't apply ... Let me rephrase that Quote a little , so that you won't see it as an issue with teaming ... <br>
<br>
Rephrase:  Respect the RTA Rules (in General), and wait a year or so to see the higher content. All that time losing members of your guild to the higher end guilds who have surpased that content, and are the ones enforcing the &quot;RTA Rules&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
Do you have any idea how many members my guild has lost because of this? I think I've lost count ... And each time someone has left, they have wound up going to ... Gues what , another guild thats farther along in game than we are. <br>
<br>
How exactly do you compete with that ? <br>
<br>
Alliance ?? Uh huh ... Anyone remember what Happened with the Clan X alliances ... As I recall that was 5 Alliance Fiasco , and when the Main Guild of that Alliance got what they wanted, they told the other Guilds to shove off, leaving the other guilds pretty much high and dry. <br>
<br>
Or Alliance , and see members leave to the other guild... or one of the Guilds Absorbed, or the Guilds Merged...  Sorry but this is something that alot of People just are to keen on ...and I've definately seen a bad merger or two.  <br>
<br>
Not to mention finding another Guild in game , that plays the same time that you do, and has somewhat similar values that your guild has, is practically impossible. <br>
<br>
While my Guild is not totally against the Idea of Alliances they are far more Difficult to do correctly, considering the above ((Yes We've actually looked and tried to set something up a few times, and the bottom fell out each time))<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Lets just make a rule(s) about it and stay consistant.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And yes if you are going to have rules ... at least be consistant... And I quote ... <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Planes, Fear, Sky, Hate:<br>
<br>
Any guild caught &quot;cleaning up&quot; on nights when a guild has already been there on respawns (IE guild goes in early clears fear, and another guild comes in and cleans up on respawn pushing the respawn time back for the next guild) will be assessed a 30 day penalty on the calender, during which said reserves will be removed and redone.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
and <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Leaving the Plane:<br>
- Once the reserving entity leaves the Plane on their Reserved Day the Plane then goes FFA/FCFS, up until 2 AM Pacific Time. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Anyone want to try and tell me that that is consistant ?  Which one Applies ... <br>
<br>
Oh, well some of you may say , that one of these is in regards to &quot;Non-Posting&quot; Entities , and the Other is in regards to &quot;Posting&quot; Entities ... <br>
<br>
I call Hogwash ... I won't quote it again ... but FFA/FCFS means any and all guilds ... NOT all guilds except posting entities. <br>
<br>
<br>
And I'm quite sure, that if one were to really look , and an accurate log had been kept, on Crimes vs Punishments done by the different guilds on server... I would be willing to say that you would see more Inconsistancies...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You do not have to be a Calendar Posting Entity to be entered into a Rotation. All it takes is for your guild/alliance, without any help from any other guild/alliance, to kill said Rotation mob (for instance: Trak) to be entered into the Rotation.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This right here , begs only one question ... and that would be WTF? ... And yes that is quite literally what I say to this ... <br>
<br>
I mean, the possibility for Guilds to be on a Rotation , yet not a Posting Entity for the Planes ??? Huh ? Excuse me , can someone please explain this to me ?  It is most definately possible to drop some of the Rotation mobs that are on the Rotation list , without Having 40 people ... Some of them without having even 30 or 36 people (if they know the right strategies or are of appropriate level etc.), Yet your trying to tell me , that that Guild Can't Reserve Hate, Fear, or Sky, cause they don't have 40+ Planesable toons ??   What type of messed up logic is that ?   <br>
<br>
Hypothetical:<br>
Yes my guild is on Rotation for Sev and Trak, thus basically reserving that Mob for us ... Yet we can't reserve Hate, Fear , or Sky ...<br>
<br>
again I say, where is the Logic ?? <br>
<br>
<br>
Next You have Rotations, which are in existance that Have 15 or 20+ Guilds on them. Thats one Kill everyone 3 - 4 months. How exactly is that fair ?   <br>
<br>
&quot;Woot , we killed Severilous, 4 times this year, and got 4 parts to the warrior epic...... To bad we still have 8 other warriors waiting for theirs&quot; <br>
<br>
Now while I don't know whether or not Severlious stands a chance of dropping more than one piece ... The point still stands ... Some of the Rotations , are Full , and Obsolete... <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
And right now its being discussed on wanting to create a rule to prevent &quot;teaming&quot; on pop flag mobs ... Why because people don't want to have &quot;Their zones&quot; overrun ... and yes thats how its being approached &quot;their zones&quot; ... the &quot;big Guilds zones&quot; ... <br>
<br>
The Big Guilds of the Server ... Are seeing their EXP holes for regular EXP or AA threatened  ... They are seeing their Cash Cow zones also being threatened, as people other than them will have access to the same zones as they do, and might just might sell whatever drop it may be for something cheaper than they would.  This might be a little unfair , but this is how the thread is coming across to me...<br>
<br>
I'm all for trying to prevent repeats of LOIO , and PoN ... but there comes a point in time , where the line of being reasonable is crossed ... and Making a rule based on the fact that a few guilds have decided to Team up to take down a PoP Flag mob, and the few guilds that are in the those Planes want to have those planes to themselves for a longer time period, is absurd. <br>
<br>
By the way, If this Rule of no teaming for PoP Flag mobs does go through, I do look forward to continueing to watch the High End Guilds Guild Requirements for the day , when I see the Requiremnt of Must be Flagged HoH , Tactics, Elemental etc...<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>but in essence what would happen is the smaller guilds get left with nothing as the bigger guilds will kill content to essentially &quot;block&quot; the smaller guilds. It happens all the time on the FFA servers. Is that what you want?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You want to know what the Really Ironic point about this comment is... <br>
<br>
Is that SO MANY PEOPLE are SO PROUD to brag about how &quot;Civilized&quot; our server is ... and that we are more &quot;Mature&quot; than other servers cause we don't have the same problems as other servers ... <br>
<br>
Yet Everytime ... and I mean EVERYTIME , someone mentions the fact that the RTA rules are obsolete, and need to be reworked for the game as It is today , not the game as it was 3 years ago ... People call this excuse .. <br>
<br>
Hypocrits ... Bunch of lousy Hypocrits ... <br>
<br>
If this server is really More &quot;Civilized&quot; and More &quot;Mature&quot; than other servers ... Then running away from the need to re-examine Rules that were made close to 3 years ago, and hiding behind the excuse of FFA Chaos is nothing more than a Political Maneuver to help ensure that your Guild stays on top, cause you know the game has massively changed , and the current Rules are more of a hinderance than they are a benefit... But hey your guild doesn't have to worry about it ... Your already past that... <br>
<br>
If this server is Indeed more &quot;Civilized&quot; and more &quot;Mature&quot; then this suggestion wouldn't scare so many people ... because people would continue to act &quot;civilized&quot; and &quot;Mature&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
Now then, I'm not saying that we should just completely throw the RTA out the Window ... I'm not saying that we should just go 100% FFA ... What I am saying , is that the Rules currently in Existance are Obsolete and need to be redone. <br>
<br>
<br>
Take a look at what rotations there are , and how many Guilds are on that rotation , and either Completely reset Rotations from scratch, so that guilds must kill the mob again to get back on it ... so that those that are on auto pass,or aren't actively interested in that mob, aren't on it... and those that are interested are ... and/or if the rotation has more than 12 guilds on it after that ... drop it ... 12 guilds on a rotation is approximately one kill every 3 months. <br>
<br>
Take a look at the requirements for becoming a posting entity ... Lower the 40+ Planesable to 24 or 30. Something that is more Realistic. <br>
With all the Content currently in game, and the bazaar, it is very easy to equip characters so that this number is within reason. <br>
<br>
With all the Content currently in game ... People might be suprised at how often Mobs are actually dropped and by the variance of guilds , based on Guild agenda's ... Again if we are more Civilized and More Mature than that of the other servers ... This should not be an issue. <br>
<br>
And if Needed ... Make one of the Requirements for being a posting entity , that each guild continue to respect the other Guilds in that if another Guild is already in zone or plane prepping for a mob or hunting, and another Guild comes in ... rather than SteamRolling the first Guild, and being an ass , they move on ... Again There is a TON of content out there now.  Again this should not be an Issue for us , if we are as Civil and Mature as we say we are ... <br>
<br>
So it all boils down to Stop Hiding behind the rules and , and Start acting like we claim to be ... <br>
<br>
<br>
My Guild will continue to follow the Rules of the RTA, as well we do see some of the benefits and the Reasoning behind it ... <br>
<br>
However, that Doesn't mean that We have to live with the rules that are already in existance, and are a hinderance to us, without at least trying to get them changed to something that is A)more feasable for us , and B) More feasable for the other Smaller Guilds on the Server ...<br>
<br>
It also doesn't mean, that we should just sit Idly by, while other Rules are made to Protect the Self Interests of the Big Guilds ... So that some day down the Road , when the Guild finally gets ready for that Content , that we could possibly be facing the same issue that we are facing now... <br>
<br>
Dytren Lang<br>
Guild Leader<br>
Sacrosanct Legion<br>
