Easy to see why the same conclusion is jumped to again right ?  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94690"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.dilligaf.com.au/faerar/faerarbanner.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mareenadeviant>Mareena Deviant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/3/03 7:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> This server prides itself on the civilised rules it imposes on guilds and individuals. Again and again I see it posted here that our server does this best.  And while some of those rules I personally believe are outdated, I agree in principle with the existence of them. <br>
<br>
So let me run this by you...<br>
<br>
2 guilds make an agreement, a CIVILISED agreement to team up and take down a mob. Success would benefit both guilds. Failure would be a learning experience for both guilds. No one else is wanting the mob, it has been up for days, therefore, the attempt inconveniences no one. Nor is it against any rules.  And hey, it works. The mob dies and 2 guilds shake hands and say thank you to each other for the CIVILISED manner in which the whole situation was handled. <br>
<br>
Forgive me, but I can't see where the principle or rules of the Rathe server have been compromised in any way.  I would have thought that maybe, just maybe, the sense of civility and co-operation shown in this instance is exactly what the Rathe rules strive for... the situation could have just as easily ended up with 2 guilds in competition for a mob, harsh words thrown, fights and 400 posts on flame board.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>cuz what will stop them from going after the rest as well.. Behemoth TT Grummus TZ VZ Saryrn etc etc...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And the point is?  <br>
<br>
I cannot help but think that the objections voiced (and let's remember the objections are coming from perhaps 2% of the Rathe population) are based on certain guilds wanting certain zones for themselves. Would someone explain why this would even be under discussion?  Are we not all entitled to play on a level playing field?<br>
<br>
The kill flagged people to HoH. You don't want us there? Sorry, bad luck... You say the trains etc are bad? Well that assumes we will be responsible for making them and is no different than saying people make trains in KC so therefore, only certain guilds should be allowed to have access to the zone.  Can you see the can of worms this would open?<br>
<br>
And might I remind everyone, that the top end guilds did not arrive on the server already set up as the top end guilds. They worked their way up, just as the rest of us are doing.  I can guarantee you that these top guilds were just as &quot;creative&quot; at times and just as determined to improve as a guild and as individual players.  If we're going to play the &quot;your guild and your guild only&quot; game, then let's abolish grouping altogether. <br>
<br>
I am extremely proud of my guild for the initiative shown in teaming up with CB on the AD kill.  I personally was not flagged for HoH as a result, which I believe is right and proper. I have not yet explored the other PoP zones to their full extent. But my guildies who were flagged have paid their dues in PoS/PoV/BoT etc and have as much right to move up the ladder as anyone else.<br>
<br>
I strongly urge the powers that be NOT to bend to pressure from a small percentage of our population.  Guilds need to grow and be challenged. Successes need to be applauded not ridiculed.  <br>
<br>
If progressing to these high end zones becomes dependent on being a member of a certain guild, then that will be a very sad day indeed for the Rathe Community.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
