Nope, it’s very clear you want to have your cake and eat it too.  Old world rotation mobs?  Two helpings please.  Hard to beat mobs that have quests to get around em?  One helping please, because it takes too long to do it by quests and we can’t beat it on our own.  And I think you’d be the one guilty of ignoring what has been said to this point, save to put your hands in your ears, say “LALALALALALA”, and chant your mantra “I don’t see it on the rotation page”, the whole while failing to acknowledge that you’re advocating gimping the system that has been in place for 3+ years.  If you need an alliance to advance, then make the alliance and stop taking double helpings of loot from the rotations you don’t need help on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I just got here ...what 'double standards' currently exist again? I forgot. Is that the double standard of teaming on a non-rotation mob (which is clearly covered as acceptable under the easily understood and written 'FCFS' convention ...you know, I gotta be pulling something outta my ass in every fun filled post!) ...or is that the double standard of applying rotation mob rules to non-rotation mobs by 'extrapolation'?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
