This is fine, I understand your point and find it a positive thing that you have chosen to do this.  However, you (as in those who have killed these mobs) need to determine a way of demarkating who is up and who has killed last.  A mob that has been up for several days is just begging to be ganked by somebody, and I suspect that despite this discussion, CB/VoLS will not be the last to assume that nobody is interested in a mob that has spent half a week unclaimed.  I suggest that you put your heads together and determine a suitable method of removing this mob from FCFS status.  It will likely not be long before complete pick-up raids start forming with people of those 35+ guilds you mentioned to take him and other PoP bosses down.<br>
